  "prompt": "Where can I update the latest FIFA squad 14 for PC offline?",
  "response": "To update the latest FIFA 14 squad for PC offline, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Find a Squad Update File**:\n   - Look for community forums, websites like SoccerGaming, MODdingWay, or FIFAMods, where FIFA enthusiasts and modders upload the latest squad update files.\n   - Make sure the file you download is compatible with FIFA 14.\n\n2. **Download the File**:\n   - Download the squad update file (typically a `.txt` or `.squad` file) to your PC.\n\n3. **Locate Your FIFA 14 Folder**:\n   - Navigate to the FIFA 14 folder on your PC. This is usually found in `Documents\\FIFA 14`.\n\n4. **Backup Existing Files**:\n   - Before making any changes, backup your existing data. Copy the files in the `FIFA 14` folder and keep them in a safe location.\n\n5. **Replace or Insert the New Squad File**:\n   - Copy the downloaded squad update file into the `FIFA 14` folder, replacing the old file if necessary.\n\n6. **Load the Updated Squads**:\n   - Launch FIFA 14.\n   - Go to the \"Customize\" menu, then \"Edit Teams\".\n   - Select \"Download Updates\" or \"Reset All Squads\" which will reflect the new data from the squad file.\n   - Alternatively, load the squads manually from within the game if the file type requires you to do so.\n\nRemember to check any instructions provided with the squad update file as the process may vary slightly depending on the source or specific file type.\n\n**Important Note**: Always ensure the files you download come from reputable sources to avoid malware or corrupted files.",
